From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Andrei V. Lepikhov" <lepihov@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Chaos mode: add missing pathkey Vars to tlist in
 prepare_sort_from_pathkeys

In chaos mode, truncate_useless_pathkeys preserves pathkeys that the
normal planner would discard.  These pathkeys may reference Vars absent
from the plan's target list (e.g., join-condition columns not in SELECT).

Rather than patching individual callers like create_gather_merge_plan,
fix this in prepare_sort_from_pathkeys itself: when find_computable_ec_member
returns NULL, find a satisfiable EC member, add its missing Vars as resjunk
TargetEntries, and retry.  This is the standard PostgreSQL mechanism for
carrying non-output sort keys through plan nodes.

This fixes the issue for all callers: create_gather_merge_plan,
create_sort_plan, create_mergejoin_plan, and any future callers.

Must be applied after patches 0001-0006.
---
 src/backend/optimizer/plan/createplan.c | 52 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 52 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/backend/optimizer/plan/createplan.c b/src/backend/optimizer/plan/createplan.c
index de6a183da79..9a7c90dd87b 100644
--- a/src/backend/optimizer/plan/createplan.c
+++ b/src/backend/optimizer/plan/createplan.c
@@ -6255,6 +6255,58 @@ prepare_sort_from_pathkeys(Plan *lefttree, List *pathkeys,
 			 * No matching tlist item; look for a computable expression.
 			 */
 			em = find_computable_ec_member(NULL, ec, tlist, relids, false);
+#ifdef CHAOS_MODE
+			if (!em)
+			{
+				/*
+				 * In chaos mode, truncate_useless_pathkeys preserves extra
+				 * pathkeys whose Vars may be absent from the target list
+				 * (e.g., join-condition columns not in SELECT).  Find a
+				 * satisfiable EC member and add its missing Vars as resjunk
+				 * TargetEntries, then retry.  This is the same mechanism
+				 * the planner uses for ORDER BY expressions not in SELECT.
+				 */
+				EquivalenceMemberIterator chaos_it;
+				EquivalenceMember *chaos_em;
+
+				setup_eclass_member_iterator(&chaos_it, ec, relids);
+				while ((chaos_em = eclass_member_iterator_next(&chaos_it)) != NULL)
+				{
+					List	   *emvars;
+					ListCell   *lc_var;
+
+					if (chaos_em->em_is_const)
+						continue;
+
+					emvars = pull_var_clause((Node *) chaos_em->em_expr,
+											 PVC_INCLUDE_AGGREGATES |
+											 PVC_INCLUDE_WINDOWFUNCS |
+											 PVC_INCLUDE_PLACEHOLDERS);
+					foreach(lc_var, emvars)
+					{
+						if (!tlist_member((Expr *) lfirst(lc_var),
+													 tlist))
+						{
+							TargetEntry *junk_tle;
+
+							junk_tle = makeTargetEntry(
+								(Expr *) copyObject(lfirst(lc_var)),
+								list_length(tlist) + 1,
+								NULL,
+								true);	/* resjunk */
+							tlist = lappend(tlist, junk_tle);
+							lefttree->targetlist = tlist;
+						}
+					}
+					list_free(emvars);
+					break;		/* used first satisfiable member */
+				}
+
+				/* Retry now that the tlist has the needed Vars */
+				em = find_computable_ec_member(NULL, ec, tlist, relids,
+											   false);
+			}
+#endif
 			if (!em)
 				elog(ERROR, "could not find pathkey item to sort");
 			pk_datatype = em->em_datatype;
